{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The electricity powering the lights in this theater"},{"time":3000,"text":"was generated just moments ago."},{"time":6000,"text":"Because the way things stand today,"},{"time":9000,"text":"electricity demand must be in constant balance"},{"time":12000,"text":"with electricity supply."},{"time":15000,"text":"If in the time that it took me to walk out here on this stage,"},{"time":18000,"text":"some tens of megawatts of wind power"},{"time":21000,"text":"stopped pouring into the grid,"},{"time":24000,"text":"the difference would have to be made up"},{"time":26000,"text":"from other generators immediately."},{"time":30000,"text":"But coal plants, nuclear plants"},{"time":33000,"text":"can't respond fast enough."},{"time":35000,"text":"A giant battery could."},{"time":37000,"text":"With a giant battery,"},{"time":39000,"text":"we'd be able to address the problem of intermittency"},{"time":42000,"text":"that prevents wind and solar"},{"time":44000,"text":"from contributing to the grid"},{"time":46000,"text":"in the same way that coal, gas and nuclear do today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"You see, the battery"},{"time":52000,"text":"is the key enabling device here."},{"time":55000,"text":"With it, we could draw electricity from the sun"},{"time":58000,"text":"even when the sun doesn't shine."},{"time":60000,"text":"And that changes everything."},{"time":63000,"text":"Because then renewables"},{"time":65000,"text":"such as wind and solar"},{"time":67000,"text":"come out from the wings,"},{"time":69000,"text":"here to center stage."},{"time":71000,"text":"Today I want to tell you about such a device."},{"time":74000,"text":"It's called the liquid metal battery."},{"time":76000,"text":"It's a new form of energy storage"},{"time":78000,"text":"that I invented at MIT"},{"time":81000,"text":"along with a team of my students"},{"time":83000,"text":"and post-docs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"Now the theme of this year's TED Conference is Full Spectrum."},{"time":88000,"text":"The OED defines spectrum"},{"time":91000,"text":"as \"The entire range of wavelengths"},{"time":94000,"text":"of electromagnetic radiation,"},{"time":96000,"text":"from the longest radio waves to the shortest gamma rays"},{"time":99000,"text":"of which the range of visible light"},{"time":102000,"text":"is only a small part.\""},{"time":104000,"text":"So I'm not here today only to tell you"},{"time":106000,"text":"how my team at MIT has drawn out of nature"},{"time":109000,"text":"a solution to one of the world's great problems."},{"time":112000,"text":"I want to go full spectrum and tell you how,"},{"time":115000,"text":"in the process of developing"},{"time":117000,"text":"this new technology,"},{"time":119000,"text":"we've uncovered some surprising heterodoxies"},{"time":122000,"text":"that can serve as lessons for innovation,"},{"time":125000,"text":"ideas worth spreading."},{"time":128000,"text":"And you know,"},{"time":130000,"text":"if we're going to get this country out of its current energy situation,"},{"time":134000,"text":"we can't just conserve our way out;"},{"time":137000,"text":"we can't just drill our way out;"},{"time":140000,"text":"we can't bomb our way out."},{"time":142000,"text":"We're going to do it the old-fashioned American way,"},{"time":144000,"text":"we're going to invent our way out,"},{"time":146000,"text":"working together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"Now let's get started."},{"time":153000,"text":"The battery was invented about 200 years ago"},{"time":156000,"text":"by a professor, Alessandro Volta,"},{"time":158000,"text":"at the University of Padua in Italy."},{"time":161000,"text":"His invention gave birth to a new field of science,"},{"time":163000,"text":"electrochemistry,"},{"time":165000,"text":"and new technologies"},{"time":167000,"text":"such as electroplating."},{"time":169000,"text":"Perhaps overlooked,"},{"time":171000,"text":"Volta's invention of the battery"},{"time":173000,"text":"for the first time also"},{"time":175000,"text":"demonstrated the utility of a professor."},{"time":177000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":179000,"text":"Until Volta, nobody could imagine"},{"time":181000,"text":"a professor could be of any use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"Here's the first battery --"},{"time":187000,"text":"a stack of coins, zinc and silver,"},{"time":190000,"text":"separated by cardboard soaked in brine."},{"time":192000,"text":"This is the starting point"},{"time":194000,"text":"for designing a battery --"},{"time":196000,"text":"two electrodes,"},{"time":198000,"text":"in this case metals of different composition,"},{"time":200000,"text":"and an electrolyte,"},{"time":202000,"text":"in this case salt dissolved in water."},{"time":204000,"text":"The science is that simple."},{"time":206000,"text":"Admittedly, I've left out a few details."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"Now I've taught you"},{"time":212000,"text":"that battery science is straightforward"},{"time":214000,"text":"and the need for grid-level storage"},{"time":216000,"text":"is compelling,"},{"time":218000,"text":"but the fact is"},{"time":220000,"text":"that today there is simply no battery technology"},{"time":223000,"text":"capable of meeting"},{"time":225000,"text":"the demanding performance requirements of the grid --"},{"time":229000,"text":"namely uncommonly high power,"},{"time":231000,"text":"long service lifetime"},{"time":233000,"text":"and super-low cost."},{"time":235000,"text":"We need to think about the problem differently."},{"time":238000,"text":"We need to think big,"},{"time":240000,"text":"we need to think cheap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242000,"text":"So let's abandon the paradigm"},{"time":244000,"text":"of let's search for the coolest chemistry"},{"time":247000,"text":"and then hopefully we'll chase down the cost curve"},{"time":249000,"text":"by just making lots and lots of product."},{"time":252000,"text":"Instead, let's invent"},{"time":254000,"text":"to the price point of the electricity market."},{"time":257000,"text":"So that means"},{"time":259000,"text":"that certain parts of the periodic table"},{"time":261000,"text":"are axiomatically off-limits."},{"time":263000,"text":"This battery needs to be made"},{"time":265000,"text":"out of earth-abundant elements."},{"time":267000,"text":"I say, if you want to make something dirt cheap,"},{"time":270000,"text":"make it out of dirt --"},{"time":272000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":274000,"text":"preferably dirt"},{"time":276000,"text":"that's locally sourced."},{"time":279000,"text":"And we need to be able to build this thing"},{"time":282000,"text":"using simple manufacturing techniques and factories"},{"time":285000,"text":"that don't cost us a fortune."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289000,"text":"So about six years ago,"},{"time":291000,"text":"I started thinking about this problem."},{"time":293000,"text":"And in order to adopt a fresh perspective,"},{"time":296000,"text":"I sought inspiration from beyond the field of electricity storage."},{"time":300000,"text":"In fact, I looked to a technology"},{"time":303000,"text":"that neither stores nor generates electricity,"},{"time":306000,"text":"but instead consumes electricity,"},{"time":308000,"text":"huge amounts of it."},{"time":310000,"text":"I'm talking about the production of aluminum."},{"time":314000,"text":"The process was invented in 1886"},{"time":316000,"text":"by a couple of 22-year-olds --"},{"time":318000,"text":"Hall in the United States and Heroult in France."},{"time":321000,"text":"And just a few short years following their discovery,"},{"time":324000,"text":"aluminum changed"},{"time":326000,"text":"from a precious metal costing as much as silver"},{"time":329000,"text":"to a common structural material."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332000,"text":"You're looking at the cell house of a modern aluminum smelter."},{"time":335000,"text":"It's about 50 feet wide"},{"time":337000,"text":"and recedes about half a mile --"},{"time":339000,"text":"row after row of cells"},{"time":342000,"text":"that, inside, resemble Volta's battery,"},{"time":345000,"text":"with three important differences."},{"time":347000,"text":"Volta's battery works at room temperature."},{"time":350000,"text":"It's fitted with solid electrodes"},{"time":353000,"text":"and an electrolyte that's a solution of salt and water."},{"time":356000,"text":"The Hall-Heroult cell"},{"time":358000,"text":"operates at high temperature,"},{"time":360000,"text":"a temperature high enough"},{"time":362000,"text":"that the aluminum metal product is liquid."},{"time":364000,"text":"The electrolyte"},{"time":366000,"text":"is not a solution of salt and water,"},{"time":368000,"text":"but rather salt that's melted."},{"time":370000,"text":"It's this combination of liquid metal,"},{"time":372000,"text":"molten salt and high temperature"},{"time":375000,"text":"that allows us to send high current through this thing."},{"time":379000,"text":"Today, we can produce virgin metal from ore"},{"time":382000,"text":"at a cost of less than 50 cents a pound."},{"time":385000,"text":"That's the economic miracle"},{"time":387000,"text":"of modern electrometallurgy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389000,"text":"It is this that caught and held my attention"},{"time":392000,"text":"to the point that I became obsessed with inventing a battery"},{"time":396000,"text":"that could capture this gigantic economy of scale."},{"time":400000,"text":"And I did."},{"time":402000,"text":"I made the battery all liquid --"},{"time":405000,"text":"liquid metals for both electrodes"},{"time":407000,"text":"and a molten salt for the electrolyte."},{"time":409000,"text":"I'll show you how."},{"time":429000,"text":"So I put low-density"},{"time":432000,"text":"liquid metal at the top,"},{"time":436000,"text":"put a high-density liquid metal at the bottom,"},{"time":442000,"text":"and molten salt in between."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448000,"text":"So now,"},{"time":450000,"text":"how to choose the metals?"},{"time":453000,"text":"For me, the design exercise"},{"time":455000,"text":"always begins here"},{"time":457000,"text":"with the periodic table,"},{"time":459000,"text":"enunciated by another professor,"},{"time":461000,"text":"Dimitri Mendeleyev."},{"time":463000,"text":"Everything we know"},{"time":465000,"text":"is made of some combination"},{"time":467000,"text":"of what you see depicted here."},{"time":470000,"text":"And that includes our own bodies."},{"time":472000,"text":"I recall the very moment one day"},{"time":475000,"text":"when I was searching for a pair of metals"},{"time":478000,"text":"that would meet the constraints"},{"time":480000,"text":"of earth abundance,"},{"time":482000,"text":"different, opposite density"},{"time":485000,"text":"and high mutual reactivity."},{"time":487000,"text":"I felt the thrill of realization"},{"time":489000,"text":"when I knew I'd come upon the answer."},{"time":494000,"text":"Magnesium for the top layer."},{"time":497000,"text":"And antimony"},{"time":499000,"text":"for the bottom layer."},{"time":502000,"text":"You know, I've got to tell you,"},{"time":504000,"text":"one of the greatest benefits of being a professor:"},{"time":507000,"text":"colored chalk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"So to produce current,"},{"time":515000,"text":"magnesium loses two electrons"},{"time":517000,"text":"to become magnesium ion,"},{"time":520000,"text":"which then migrates across the electrolyte,"},{"time":522000,"text":"accepts two electrons from the antimony,"},{"time":525000,"text":"and then mixes with it to form an alloy."},{"time":528000,"text":"The electrons go to work"},{"time":530000,"text":"in the real world out here,"},{"time":533000,"text":"powering our devices."},{"time":539000,"text":"Now to charge the battery,"},{"time":542000,"text":"we connect a source of electricity."},{"time":545000,"text":"It could be something like a wind farm."},{"time":549000,"text":"And then we reverse the current."},{"time":553000,"text":"And this forces magnesium to de-alloy"},{"time":558000,"text":"and return to the upper electrode,"},{"time":561000,"text":"restoring the initial constitution of the battery."},{"time":566000,"text":"And the current passing between the electrodes"},{"time":569000,"text":"generates enough heat to keep it at temperature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"It's pretty cool,"},{"time":575000,"text":"at least in theory."},{"time":577000,"text":"But does it really work?"},{"time":579000,"text":"So what to do next?"},{"time":581000,"text":"We go to the laboratory."},{"time":583000,"text":"Now do I hire seasoned professionals?"},{"time":587000,"text":"No, I hire a student"},{"time":590000,"text":"and mentor him,"},{"time":592000,"text":"teach him how to think about the problem,"},{"time":595000,"text":"to see it from my perspective"},{"time":597000,"text":"and then turn him loose."},{"time":599000,"text":"This is that student, David Bradwell,"},{"time":601000,"text":"who, in this image,"},{"time":603000,"text":"appears to be wondering if this thing will ever work."},{"time":606000,"text":"What I didn't tell David at the time"},{"time":608000,"text":"was I myself wasn't convinced it would work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"But David's young and he's smart"},{"time":613000,"text":"and he wants a Ph.D.,"},{"time":615000,"text":"and he proceeds to build --"},{"time":617000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":619000,"text":"He proceeds to build"},{"time":621000,"text":"the first ever liquid metal battery"},{"time":623000,"text":"of this chemistry."},{"time":625000,"text":"And based on David's initial promising results,"},{"time":628000,"text":"which were paid"},{"time":630000,"text":"with seed funds at MIT,"},{"time":633000,"text":"I was able to attract major research funding"},{"time":636000,"text":"from the private sector"},{"time":638000,"text":"and the federal government."},{"time":640000,"text":"And that allowed me to expand my group to 20 people,"},{"time":643000,"text":"a mix of graduate students, post-docs"},{"time":645000,"text":"and even some undergraduates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"And I was able to attract really, really good people,"},{"time":650000,"text":"people who share my passion"},{"time":652000,"text":"for science and service to society,"},{"time":654000,"text":"not science and service for career building."},{"time":658000,"text":"And if you ask these people"},{"time":660000,"text":"why they work on liquid metal battery,"},{"time":662000,"text":"their answer would hearken back"},{"time":664000,"text":"to President Kennedy's remarks"},{"time":666000,"text":"at Rice University in 1962"},{"time":669000,"text":"when he said -- and I'm taking liberties here --"},{"time":671000,"text":"\"We choose to work on grid-level storage,"},{"time":673000,"text":"not because it is easy,"},{"time":675000,"text":"but because it is hard.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":677000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":684000,"text":"So this is the evolution of the liquid metal battery."},{"time":687000,"text":"We start here with our workhorse one watt-hour cell."},{"time":690000,"text":"I called it the shotglass."},{"time":692000,"text":"We've operated over 400 of these,"},{"time":695000,"text":"perfecting their performance with a plurality of chemistries --"},{"time":698000,"text":"not just magnesium and antimony."},{"time":700000,"text":"Along the way we scaled up to the 20 watt-hour cell."},{"time":703000,"text":"I call it the hockey puck."},{"time":705000,"text":"And we got the same remarkable results."},{"time":707000,"text":"And then it was onto the saucer."},{"time":709000,"text":"That's 200 watt-hours."},{"time":711000,"text":"The technology was proving itself"},{"time":713000,"text":"to be robust and scalable."},{"time":716000,"text":"But the pace wasn't fast enough for us."},{"time":718000,"text":"So a year and a half ago,"},{"time":720000,"text":"David and I,"},{"time":722000,"text":"along with another research staff-member,"},{"time":724000,"text":"formed a company"},{"time":726000,"text":"to accelerate the rate of progress"},{"time":728000,"text":"and the race to manufacture product."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730000,"text":"So today at LMBC,"},{"time":732000,"text":"we're building cells 16 inches in diameter"},{"time":734000,"text":"with a capacity of one kilowatt-hour --"},{"time":736000,"text":"1,000 times the capacity"},{"time":739000,"text":"of that initial shotglass cell."},{"time":741000,"text":"We call that the pizza."},{"time":743000,"text":"And then we've got a four kilowatt-hour cell on the horizon."},{"time":746000,"text":"It's going to be 36 inches in diameter."},{"time":748000,"text":"We call that the bistro table,"},{"time":750000,"text":"but it's not ready yet for prime-time viewing."},{"time":752000,"text":"And one variant of the technology"},{"time":754000,"text":"has us stacking these bistro tabletops into modules,"},{"time":758000,"text":"aggregating the modules into a giant battery"},{"time":761000,"text":"that fits in a 40-foot shipping container"},{"time":763000,"text":"for placement in the field."},{"time":765000,"text":"And this has a nameplate capacity of two megawatt-hours --"},{"time":768000,"text":"two million watt-hours."},{"time":770000,"text":"That's enough energy"},{"time":772000,"text":"to meet the daily electrical needs"},{"time":774000,"text":"of 200 American households."},{"time":776000,"text":"So here you have it, grid-level storage:"},{"time":779000,"text":"silent, emissions-free,"},{"time":782000,"text":"no moving parts,"},{"time":784000,"text":"remotely controlled,"},{"time":786000,"text":"designed to the market price point"},{"time":789000,"text":"without subsidy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792000,"text":"So what have we learned from all this?"},{"time":794000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":800000,"text":"So what have we learned from all this?"},{"time":802000,"text":"Let me share with you"},{"time":804000,"text":"some of the surprises, the heterodoxies."},{"time":807000,"text":"They lie beyond the visible."},{"time":809000,"text":"Temperature:"},{"time":811000,"text":"Conventional wisdom says set it low,"},{"time":813000,"text":"at or near room temperature,"},{"time":815000,"text":"and then install a control system to keep it there."},{"time":818000,"text":"Avoid thermal runaway."},{"time":820000,"text":"Liquid metal battery is designed to operate at elevated temperature"},{"time":823000,"text":"with minimum regulation."},{"time":826000,"text":"Our battery can handle the very high temperature rises"},{"time":829000,"text":"that come from current surges."},{"time":833000,"text":"Scaling: Conventional wisdom says"},{"time":836000,"text":"reduce cost by producing many."},{"time":838000,"text":"Liquid metal battery is designed to reduce cost"},{"time":841000,"text":"by producing fewer, but they'll be larger."},{"time":844000,"text":"And finally, human resources:"},{"time":846000,"text":"Conventional wisdom says"},{"time":848000,"text":"hire battery experts,"},{"time":850000,"text":"seasoned professionals,"},{"time":852000,"text":"who can draw upon their vast experience and knowledge."},{"time":855000,"text":"To develop liquid metal battery,"},{"time":857000,"text":"I hired students and post-docs and mentored them."},{"time":860000,"text":"In a battery,"},{"time":862000,"text":"I strive to maximize electrical potential;"},{"time":865000,"text":"when mentoring,"},{"time":867000,"text":"I strive to maximize human potential."},{"time":869000,"text":"So you see,"},{"time":871000,"text":"the liquid metal battery story"},{"time":873000,"text":"is more than an account"},{"time":875000,"text":"of inventing technology,"},{"time":877000,"text":"it's a blueprint"},{"time":879000,"text":"for inventing inventors, full-spectrum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}